# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# RIS::Journeys v1 (historical data — used for GET /find to resolve
# a trainNumber + travelDate to a journeyID)
# Subscribe at: https://developers.deutschebahn.com/db-api-marketplace/apis/product/ris-journeys-transporteure
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
RIS_V1_CLIENT_ID=
RIS_V1_API_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# RIS::Journeys v2 (real-time journey details — used for GET /{journeyID}
# to fetch all stops with cancellation status)
# Subscribe at: https://developers.deutschebahn.com/db-api-marketplace/apis/product/ris-journeys-transporteure
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
RIS_V2_CLIENT_ID=
RIS_V2_API_KEY=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Booking data source
# - In JSON mode the backend reads this Excel file at boot.
# - In Redis mode this is only read by `pnpm seed:bookings` to populate
#   the Upstash hash; the deployed backend never touches the file.
# Defaults to ../.local/Bookingdata_UPLOAD_custom_auftragsnummer.xlsx
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# BOOKING_DATA_PATH=/absolute/path/to/Bookingdata.xlsx

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# Persistence backend
#
# Values:
#   json   — default. Local Excel + JSON files under DATA_DIR (./data).
#   redis  — Upstash Redis via REST for both help-requests and the
#            bookings reference data. Use this for serverless or
#            ephemeral-filesystem hosts (Render free, Vercel, Lambda).
#            Seed the bookings hash once with `pnpm seed:bookings`.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------
# PERSISTENCE_BACKEND=json
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
# UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
